South Africa’s government sold a total of R3.9 billion ($263.7 million) of its 2030, 2032 and 2048 bonds on Tuesday. Yields were mostly higher compared with previous auctions. R2030 BOND: January 31, 2030 – 8% coupon R2032 BOND: March 31, 2032 – 6.25% coupon R2048 BOND: February 28, 2048 – 8.75% coupon